{
  "stem": "8775.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was bar mitzvahed in, in Szolnok, in the conservative temple, which now serves as a museum and has beautiful stained glass windows.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was really one of the most beautiful synagogues in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, that street where the synagogue stands, there were three other churches, and it kind of symbolized the common faith among all those churches, which of course, did not happen to be true.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Roman Catholic church was just a little bit further up from the synagogue, and there was the Lutheran church.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was also the Calvinist church, named from John Calvin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And everything seemed pretty peaceful in those years, obviously.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As I mentioned to you, my mother's uncle and his wife, they went together, and she-- with their dog.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he would escort her to the Roman Catholic church.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He would stand in front of the church and wait for her to finish up.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then they walked right home, and the same thing happened on the Jewish holiday.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She went with him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He went into the temple.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She waited for him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that's how-- that's how they lived.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That is correct.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I started seeing the change as soon as I finished the elementary school, which was in 1940.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was time for me to go to what is called the gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A gymnasium is a high school preparatory to college.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's a college preparation course, mainly with Latin, and perhaps French or German, some other language, and heavy science.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I couldn't get into the local, to, to the-- to the state gymnasium, simply because there was a law passed, obviously by those parties, the right-wing parties.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the law said that-- it was called Numerus Clausus, which means a closed number.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
